Epiproct (
Figs.
5 – 8
): Length ca. 60 μm (medially), greatest width ca. 160 μm, lateral sides ca. 120 μm. Epiproct triangular with broad triangular posterior indentation in dorsal view and plump in lateral view. Dorsum of epiproct with three irregular rows of warty and sharp spines arranged on posterior margins. Epiproct apex tongueshaped and smooth (
Fig. 7
).

Aedeagus (
Figs.
5 – 10
): Enlarged with a rounded, brownish, lower lobe laterally and a ventral patch of small to median-sized spines. A band of dense setae lies anterior to an upraised lobe (
Figs.
5 – 8
). Ventrolaterally, a pair of sharp stylus originating from a hook shaped sclerite (
Figs.
9 – 10
).
